ultiplying the opportunities for pleasure, but it has great difficulty in generating joy.', 3779, 0), (483528, 'It may not always be profitable at first for businesses to be online, but it is certainly going to be unprofitable not to be online.', 13711, 0), (483529, 'Defect-free software does not exist.', 70111, 0), (483530, 'I''m a farm boy. I would rather live in that time when you had to provide for your family. I don''t know. I''m a country kid, so I don''t like modern technology.', 72622, 0), (483531, 'It''s not that we use technology, we live technology.', 26193, 0), (483532, 'Negative and pessimistic views of technology have always existed. I can just imagine some pessimistic Sumerian in 3500 B.C. screaming about the evils of the wheel.', 70518, 0), (483533, 'I''m an optimist about the power of technology to transform lives for the better.', 75277, 0), (483534, 'If cheap immigrant labor is made unavailable, employers can hire Americans at a higher wage, or replace low-wage immigrant workers with technology and automation, which will create a smaller number of skilled jobs for Americans.', 72558, 0), (483535, 'There are no morals about technology at all. Technology expands our ways of thinking about things, expands our ways of doing things. If we''re bad people we use technology for bad purposes and if we''re good people we use it for good purposes.', 2920, 0), (483536, 'Broadband access is the great equalizer, leveling the playing field so that every willing and able person, no matter their station in life, has access to the information and tools necessary to achieve the American Dream.', 69564, 0), (483537, 'I believe the auto industry is a competition of human resources, competition of funding, competition of technology - and the competition is international.', 69563, 0), (483538, 'In school all I wanted to do was build technology. That''s what I loved.', 70532, 0), (483539, 'Although I loved working on technology - I''ve always been a computer geek at hear